meanings.sent1: The ancient ruins preexisted the modern city.
meanings.sent2: The dinosaurs preexisted humans on Earth.
meanings.sent3: The idea of time travel to a time that preexisted our own is fascinating.
meanings.sent4: Her love for him seemed to preexist any logical explanation.
meanings.sent5: The legend of the lost civilization preexisted in the minds of many explorers.

meanings.definition: To have existed prior to something else
meanings.sent1: The ancient civilization preexisted the one we study in history books.
meanings.sent2: The ancient manuscripts preexisted the printing press.
meanings.sent3: The concept of virtual reality preexisted the technology to create it.
meanings.sent4: His reputation for honesty preexisted him wherever he went.
meanings.sent5: The ancient prophecy seemed to preexist the events that followed.
